              		                            			NMAP


WHAT’S NMAP?

Nmap is an open-source network scanning and security auditing tool used to discover live hosts, open ports, running services, operating systems, and vulnerabilities in a network. It is widely used in cybersecurity, ethical hacking, and penetration testing for network reconnaissance and security assessment.




NMAP INSTALLATION / CONFIGURATION & SETUP

1)  Check Whether Nmap is Already Installed
•	Open terminal and type:
		-   nmap –version

2)    Install Nmap
•	For Debian / Ubuntu / Kali Linux : 
-   sudo apt update
 		-   sudo apt install nmap
•	For Fedora : 
-   sudo dnf install nmap

•	For CentOS / RHEL : 
-   sudo yum install nmap

3)	 Verify Installation  
-   nmap -v
        [OR]
-   nmap --version

  THIS CONFIRMS THAT NMAP IS INSTALLED SUCCESSFULLY.




